### Description

I want to use some postcss plugin. so I create angular v17 application (with vite).

I add postcss.config.js to root of the project and write this:

```
const myPlugin = require('./my-plugin');
module.exports = {
    plugins: [
      myPlugin(),
    ]
 };
```
my-plugin.js:
```
module.exports = (opts = {}) => {
  return {
    postcssPlugin: "MyCustomPlugin",
    Once(root, { result, postcss }) {
      root.walkDecls((declaration) => {
        console.log("yay");
        // Your transformation code here
      });
    },
  };
};
module.exports.postcss = true;
```

In `serve` command I get the console, but in `build` command I don't see the console outputs. (i use `--verbose` flag).

Also when I use plugins like those, it's seems that the angular-vite is ignore those plugins:
```
      postcssGlobalData({
        files: ['./node_modules/open-props/media.min.css'],
      }),
      postcssCustomMedia(/* pluginOptions */),
``` 

